  "assumptions": [],
  "summary": "A mole is a count: $N_A = 6.02214076\\times10^{23}$ particles per mole (exact since the 2019 SI redefinition). Multiplying an amount in moles by $N_A$ gives a pure number of particles — the moles cancel the per-mole of $N_A$, leaving a dimensionless count, which the machine confirms.",
